## Conversation
Continuation of the ts-v2 shared-cleanup. User: "move the agents code too -- it should be in another PR on the stack." This is PR7, stacked on andrew/ts-v2-server-worker-shared (PR6).

## What & why
The GenAI/agent observability API is server-only. Evidence: client bindings (RemoteHTTPTraceServer/stainless) implement ZERO agent methods; no weave-client module calls any agent query; the only consumers are weave.trace_server.* (query builders, OTel extraction, chat_view, clickhouse impl) + core's agent_scoring_worker. It lived in weave/shared ONLY because the monolithic TraceServerInterface(Protocol) typed 9 agent methods using agent_types, and types.py is fused with schema/semconv/constants (it imports all three). So ~1900 lines of ClickHouse schema + GenAI semantic conventions + query-builder constants sat in the client SDK's dependency closure.

